※Be careful not to hit Jean with your attacks. If you defeat
them, it's game over.

This is an action RPG boss battle. Avoid the enemy's attacks
and strike with the A key. While holding the D key, you can
move with your direction fixed.

If either your stamina or health reaches 0 due to the
enemy's attacks, you will be defeated. Generally, ranged
attacks will reduce health, while contact will reduce
stamina.

When you come into contact with the enemy, you'll be held
and continue to take damage until you succeed at the timing
bar. Let me show you the timing bar.

Stopping on yellow is a success, stopping on red is a
critical. If you stop on yellow, you'll take damage and be
released; stopping on red will halve the damage and release
you.

Furthermore, taking damage to your stamina from the enemy
will put you in a [Color_14]state of arousal\C[0], reducing
the number of slashes during your attack. A heart mark will
appear on your status while in this state.

Arousal can be removed by walking around a set number of
steps. It can also be removed by achieving a critical to
shake off the enemy. If possible, aim to stop on red.

.Learn the enemy's attack patterns. The enemy's attacks have
patterns. Focus on dodging first to learn them.

.Make use of the D key's direction lock. Locking your
direction makes it easier to attack and dodge. Attacking
while moving backwards can make the fight easier.

.Use healing items and skills. There are no usage limits for
healing items and skills (like deep breaths). You can heal
and push through if necessary.

.Use Action Ease. By turning on Action Ease from the
options, the difficulty level will significantly decrease.
There are no downsides.
